'''2010年美国股市闪崩事件'''<ref>[http://www.cs.toronto.edu/~qiwang/us-stock-interactive-intraday-chart?s=spy&d=20100506 Interactive Intraday Chart of the SP500 Index on May 6, 2010] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170220175411/http://www.cs.toronto.edu/~qiwang/us-stock-interactive-intraday-chart/?s=spy&d=20100506 |date=February 20, 2017 }}, University of Toronto, June 5, 2010</ref><ref name=phillips-5-11-10>{{citation |url=https://blogs.wsj.com/marketbeat/2010/05/11/nasdaq-heres-our-timeline-of-the-flash-crash/ |title=Nasdaq: Here's Our Timeline of the Flash Crash |date=May 11, 2010 |work=Wall Street Journal |first=Matt |last=Phillips |accessdate=2021-02-25 |archive-date=2020-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200724144010/https://blogs.wsj.com/marketbeat/2010/05/11/nasdaq-heres-our-timeline-of-the-flash-crash/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Vaughan |first1=Liam |title=The Work-From-Home Trader Who Shook Global Markets |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2020-05-13/new-book-shares-more-details-on-trader-blamed-for-flash-crash?sref=9YK1BnKg |publisher=Bloomberg |access-date=15 May 2020 |archive-date=2020-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200525070950/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2020-05-13/new-book-shares-more-details-on-trader-blamed-for-flash-crash?sref=9YK1BnKg }}</ref>，简称'''2010年闪崩事件'''，是发生于2010年5月6日的一次美国股票市场[[股災|崩溃事件]]，开始于美国东部时间当日下午2时32份，持续了大约36分钟。[[道琼斯工业平均指数|道琼斯工业平均指数]]在这段时间内由10,460点开始急剧下跌，在五分钟之内跌至9,870点附近，不过几分钟后又迅速回升。事件源于位于英国的一位名叫纳文德·辛·萨劳（Navinder Singh Sarao）的交易员通过[[高频交易|高频交易]]短时间大量下单卖出操控指数。五年后，他在英国被抓获，然后被引渡至美国以控电信及商品交易诈欺罪指控。<ref name="Traders_Magazine_2015">{{citation |title=Post Flash Crash, Regulators Still Use Bicycles To Catch Ferraris: Blaming the Flash Crash on a UK man who lives with his parents is like blaming lightning for starting a fire |work=Traders Magazine Online News |date=April 24, 2015 |access-date=April 25, 2014 |first=John |last=Bates |url=http://www.tradersmagazine.com/news/technology/post-flash-crash-regulators-still-use-bicycles-to-catch-ferraris-113762-1.html?ET=tradersmagazine%3Ae4256762%3A1181926a%3A&st=email |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125134559/http://www.tradersmagazine.com/news/technology/post-flash-crash-regulators-still-use-bicycles-to-catch-ferraris-113762-1.html?ET=tradersmagazine%3Ae4256762%3A1181926a%3A&st=email |archive-date=January 25, 2018 }}</ref><ref name="CFTC_2014">{{citation |title=The Flash Crash: The Impact of High Frequency Trading on an Electronic Market |url=http://www.cftc.gov/ucm/groups/public/@economicanalysis/documents/file/oce_flashcrash0314.pdf |access-date=April 24, 2015 |date=May 5, 2014 |first1=Andrei |last1=Kirilenko |first2=Albert S. |last2=Kyle |first3=Mehrdad |last3=Samadi |last4=Tuzun |first4=Tugkan |archive-date=2015-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402131543/http://www.cftc.gov/ucm/groups/public/@economicanalysis/documents/file/oce_flashcrash0314.pdf }}</ref>

